# Project Configuration for Claude Code

## Package Management
- Always use `uv` instead of `pip` for Python package management
- Use `uv sync` to install dependencies from pyproject.toml (auto-creates venv)
- Use `uv add <package>` to add new dependencies
- Use `uv run` for running Python scripts

## IDE
- User uses PyCharm - no need to run `source .venv/bin/activate` as PyCharm handles virtual environment activation automatically

## Project Context
This project analyzes user events from Confluent Cloud Kafka to extract user journey insights using LLMs (GPT-5-nano and Claude Haiku 4.5 via AWS Bedrock).
